# STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURE (SOP): Glaucoma Referral and Monitoring Pathway
**Document ID:** OP-PATH-04
**Version:** 3.1
**Owner:** Glaucoma Clinical Lead
**Last Review:** Oct 2025 | **Next Review:** Oct 2027

## 1. Scope
This pathway applies to all adult patients referred with suspected or confirmed Glaucoma or Ocular Hypertension (OHT) at Bristol Eye Hospital.

## 2. Referral Management
* **Urgent (1-2 weeks):** IOP > 32mmHg, suspected acute angle closure, or rapid field loss.
* **Routine (18 weeks):** Suspected POAG or OHT not meeting urgent criteria.

## 3. Monitoring Intervals (NICE NG81)
| Patient Risk Category | IOP Frequency | VF / OCT Frequency |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Low Risk (Stable)** | 12 months | 12-24 months |
| **Medium Risk** | 6 months | 6-12 months |
| **High Risk (Advanced)** | 2-4 months | 4-6 months |

## 4. Virtual Clinic Eligibility
Patients may be transitioned to the **Glaucoma Virtual Clinic** if they meet the following criteria:
1. Stable disease for > 2 consecutive visits.
2. IOP controlled within target range.
3. Patient able to perform reliable visual fields.
*Note: High-risk/Advanced patients are NOT eligible for virtual monitoring.*

